record_data.record_plain_text: NORTHAMPTON GENERATING COMPANY, L.P. REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCES SERVICE Northampton Generating Company, L.P. ("Northampton") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from an electric generation facility located in Northampton, Pennsylvania ("Facility") to PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth Northampton's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Service from the Facility to PJM, pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Service. Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on the date authorized by the FERC. REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The annual revenue requirement is $418,000. The monthly charge to PJM is $418,000 / 12 = $34,833.33.
